name: Consultation
description: Collection of clinical data during the main consultation

name: Registration
description: Initial data collection for a patient, not specific to any program

name: Triage
description: Collection of limited data prior to a more thorough examination

name: HIV Consultation
description: Collection of HIV-specific data during the main consultation

name: CWC Enrollment
description: Enrollment of child onto MCH program

name: CWC Consultation
description: Collection of child data during MCH visit

name: MCH Child HEI Exit
description: Reasons that child is exited from HEI

name: MCH Child Discontinuation
description: Discontinuation of child from MCH program

name: MCH Mother Enrollment
description: Enrollment of mother onto MCH program

name: MCH Mother Consultation
description: Collection of mother data during MCH visit

name: MCH Mother Discontinuation
description: Discontinuation of mother from MCH program

name: External P-Smart
description: Holds data read from smart card and  belong to other facilities/systems

name: PrEP Enrollment
description: Enrollment of client onto PrEP program

name: PrEP Consultation
description: Collection of client data during PREP visit

name: PrEP Behavior Risk Assessment
description: Collection of client data for PrEP eligibility

name: PrEP Client Discontinuation
description: Discontinuation of client from PrEP program

name: Fertility Intention Screening
description: Handles KP Pregnancy and FP screening

name: KP Discontinuation
description: Records information about KP client discontinuation

name: KP HIV Status
description: Records information about KP Hiv Status

name: KP Diagnosis and Treatment
description: Handles KP Diagnosis and treatment plan

name: KP Contact
description: Records extra registration details for kp

name: Admission
description: Indicates that the patient has been admitted for inpatient care, and is not expected to leave the hospital unless discharged.

name: Check In
description: Indicates the patient has done the required paperwork and check-in to begin a visit to the clinic/hospital.

name: Discharge
description: Indicates that a patient's inpatient care at the hospital is ending, and they are expected to leave soon.

name: Visit Note
description: Encounter where a full or abbreviated examination is done, usually leading to a presumptive or confirmed diagnosis, recorded by the examining clinician.

name: Check Out
description: The patient is explicitly leaving the hospital/clinic. (Usually no formal encounter is captured for this.)

name: Transfer
description: Indicates that a patient is being transferred into a different department within the hospital. (Transfers out of the hospital should not use this encounter type.)

name: DM HTN Initial
description: Used for collecting Initial encounter information

name: DM HTN discontinue patient
description: DM HTN discontinue patient from care from this facility

name: COVID-19 Assessment Encounter
description: A visit encounter that provides assessment questions for covid-10 vaccination and exposure

name: Generalized Anxiety Disorder Assessment
description: Anxiety Screening using Generalized Anxiety Disorder Assessment (GAD-7)
